rs-trafilatura and web-page-classifier — MIT OR Apache-2.0 (used under Apache-2.0)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Author:  Murrough Foley
Sources: https://github.com/Murrough-Foley/rs-trafilatura
         https://github.com/Murrough-Foley/web-page-classifier

rs-trafilatura — DERIVED FROM at the CODE LEVEL (attribution required). The shipped
Rust extraction crate packages/trafilaturacore/native/ is a simplified fork of
rs-trafilatura's LIVE extraction path: the extraction orchestration and content-node
cascade (extract.rs), the fallback/baseline rescues (extractor/fallback.rs), the
content selectors (selector/*), doc-cleaning (html_processing.rs), link density
(link_density.rs), the DOM helpers (dom.rs), the 3-stage page-type cascade + URL
heuristics + HTML-signal refinement + the 7 per-type extraction profiles + confidence
rules + the 89 numeric classifier features (page_type/*) are ported/transcribed from
it. Per Apache-2.0 §4, changes were made: the crate is a simplified fork (spider,
CLIs, Markdown output, ONNX, and the embedded model removed; a preserve-markup
serializer, a pure-Rust XGBoost-JSON GBDT evaluator, and napi-rs v3 bindings added).

web-page-classifier — CONSULTED (courtesy). Referenced for the page-type feature set
and the pure-Rust tree-evaluator pattern; trafilaturacore's classifier is independently
implemented and its model is trained fresh from WCXB, so no web-page-classifier code
(and none of its embedded model binary) ships.

Both are dual-licensed MIT OR Apache-2.0; used here under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

